body:
Currently, a compilation error is thrown when a dynamic array of class objects is declared as `rand`.
Here is an example:
```systemverilog
class Cls;
  rand int x;
endclass

class unconstrained_cls_dynamic_array_test;
  rand Cls dynamic_array_1d[];
  function new();
    dynamic_array_1d = new[5];
    foreach (dynamic_array_1d[i]) begin
      dynamic_array_1d[i] = new;
    end
  endfunction
endclass

module t_randomize_array;
  unconstrained_cls_dynamic_array_test dynamic_class;

  initial begin
    dynamic_class = new();
    if (dynamic_class.randomize() != 1) $stop;
    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end

endmodule
```
It throws the following error:
```
/Vrand_class_arr___024unit__03a__03aunconstrained_cls_dynamic_array_test__Vclpkg__DepSet_h3998fff8__0.cpp:29:13: error: no viable overloaded '='
            = VL_RANDOM_RNG_I(__Vm_rng);
            ^ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
```
